South Africa Says About 23.6 Million Registered for Local Elections in May

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-03-22T09:19:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/south-africa-says-about-23-6-million-registered-for-local-elections-in-may.html
South Africa ’s Independent
 Electoral Commission  said about 23.6 million people have
registered for local elections that will be held on May 18.  There will be almost 20,900 voting stations across the
country, Pansy Tlakula, South Africa’s chief electoral officer,
told lawmakers in  Cape Town  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in Cape Town at 
